comments: Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) brings his hand towards Edwards' (MIN) arm, and the contact during the shot near the rim is marginal.
Holmgren (OKC) cleanly deflects the ball away from Gobert (MIN) and Edwards (MIN) during rebounding.

Towns (MIN) raises his right arm to pursue the rebound, and the contact with Williams' (OKC) head is marginal.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Williams (OKC) slides his pivot foot after his gather.
Williams (OKC) brings his forearm towards Edwards' (MIN) front and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Alexander-Walker (MIN) is moving alongside Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together at the same spot.
Towns (MIN) legally contests Williams' (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Wallace (OKC) commits a take foul on Edwards (MIN).
Wallace (OKC) moves alongside Alexander-Walker's (MIN) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) applies his forearm to McDaniels' (MIN) side, and the contact during the put back attempt is marginal.
Alexander-Walker (MIN) exits the paint within three seconds.
Gobert (MIN) moves alongside Williams' (OKC) path and legally contests the driving shot attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) and Edwards (MIN) come together at the same spot, and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Wallace (OKC) commits a take foul on Towns (MIN).
Edwards (MIN) extends his arm forward into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and initiates contact that affects his SQBR.
Wiggins (OKC) commits a take foul on Alexander-Walker (MIN).
